args: Is there anything I can do to help,\n{player_name}?
I just want to DO something.
You've all given me so much—\nincluding a new home.
I want to return the favor.
Well, that's really nice of you,\nbut we don't need anything in return.
But everyone else is making a\ncontribution; I must do so as well.
I'll do anything—just let me know.
We could use another set of hands\nwhen it comes to cleaning the castle?
Just point me to the mop!
Actually, I can chip in as well;\nmy schedule is remarkably light right now.
I'll start sweeping in this direction,\n{player_name}.
Then I'll work the opposite way.
Look out, dust! Here I come!
Heh. She must really be enjoying helping\nif she's started sing...ing...
It's me. Cleo. Why did you stop sweeping?
Yes, you stopped and stared at Felicia—\nin a rather slack-jawed manner, may I add.
Sorry! Sorry. I just found myself so...\ncaptivated looking at her.
I know she was just pushing a broom,\nbut it seemed like she was dancing.
*sigh* We'll make little progress if you\nlet yourself be so easily distracted.
Let's leave the cleaning for now, Felicia.\nPerhaps you could help me with the\ncooking instead?
Are you good at cooking, Felicia?
I'd say I'm reasonably competent—\nthough likely not as good as you.
That will have to do. In any case,\nI'd like you to prepare the vegetables.
Right! Let me just wash them first...
(She appears to have this under control.\nI'll get started on the soup.)
Felicia, I'm going to need you to...
(All she's doing is preparing the food,\nyet her every movement is...beautiful.)
Whew! I almost paid a steep price\nfor being captivated by you.
Your movements as you worked made it\nlook like you were dancing.
Like I was dancing...\nWait, WAS I dancing?!
Whatever you did, it was stunning.\nI couldn't take my eyes off you.
My family used to say I was dancing\nas I helped with things.
I used to spend almost the entire day\ndancing, and now it seems I do so the\nrest of the time without thinking.
And yet I love it, so I've never thought\nof it as bothersome in the slightest.
But as a result, the motions associated\nwith dancing come out in my daily life.
I wonder if that was what happened when\nwe were cleaning? Ugh. I'm so sorry.
It is our fault for becoming distracted.
Old habits are hard things to break out of.\nYou shouldn't feel bad.
But if this is how every attempt to help is\ngoing to end, there's no point in it!
The next time I help,\nI'll be certain not to dance!
I'll be fine. In fact, here! Watch me\nsort the cutlery without dancing.
Now it looks like your joints have locked.\nThere must be some kind of happy\nmedium we can find here.
I worried that would happen.\nYou were getting too tense.
Just assist me the way you\nnormally would. I'll be careful not\nto be distracted.
